headline: Ugg Dupes Case Narrows What’s Trade Dress Protectable
summary: Ugg parent Deckers Outdoor Brands sued dupes retailer Quince, and a federal judge has ruled on what's entitled to trade dress protection.

headline: Deckers (DECK) Stock Trades Up, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of footwear and apparel conglomerate Deckers (NYSE:DECK) jumped 3.1% in the afternoon session after an analyst from UBS maintained a "Buy" rating on the shares, signaling continued confidence in the company despite a minor adjustment to its price target.

headline: UBS Maintains Bullish Outlook on Deckers Outdoor Corporation (DECK) as Analysts Monitor HOKA’s U.S. Growth Recovery
summary: Fisher Asset Management holds $755,502 worth of Deckers Outdoor Corporation (NYSE:DECK) shares, helping it secure a place on our list of billionaire Ken Fisher’s 10 consumer stock picks with the highest upside potential.
